IMG Worldwide Seeking $350 Million of Loans to Refinance Debt

-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   I d z e l i s
-- 
2011-05-20T19:30:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-20/img-worldwide-seeking-350-million-of-loans-to-refinance-debt.html
IMG Worldwide Inc., the sports agency
that represents Tiger Woods and  Roger Federer , is seeking $350
million of loans to refinance debt.  The media-management company owned by Forstmann Little &
Co. is offering a five-year $300 million term loan B and a 4
1/2-year $50 million revolving credit line, according to data
compiled by Bloomberg.  JPMorgan Chase & Co. is arranging the debt for New York-
based IMG, with a lender call scheduled for May 24 at 9:30 a.m.
in New York, the data show.  IMG is rated B2 rated by Moody’s Investors Service and B by
 Standard & Poor’s . High-yield, high-risk, or junk, debt is
ranked below Baa3 by Moody’s Investors Service and less than
BBB- by Standard & Poor’s.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christine Idzelis in  New York  at 
